 - Introducing the super cute and quick and easy to make Minion beanie and diaper cover with suspender straps. This CROCHET PATTERN includes instruction for both pieces in Newborn to 2 Months, 2 to 6 Months, 6 to 12 Months and 12 to 24+/48 Months. - Great for everyday wear, as a gift or as a photography prop. It's hard to resist these Minion hats! - This pattern is available in both US and UK Terms. 



{ P A T T E R N - I N F O } 
- Instructions for a hat in 4 sizes (Newborn-2 Months, 2-6 Months, 6-12 Months, 12-48 Months); - Minion Eye(s); - Tongue; - 3 Styles of Minion Hair; - Mini-bow to make a girl minion; - Adjustable Diaper Cover with adjustable suspenders in 4 sizes (Newborn to 2 Months, 2 to 6 Months, 6 to 12 Months and 12 to 24+ Months); - This pattern is suitable for a beginner (familiar with basic stitches). 



 { M A T E R I A L S - N E E D E D } 
 - #4 (worsted / medium weight / 10-ply) yarn in yellow (less than 100g), and small amounts of black, white and grey/silver. - #4 (worsted / medium weight / 10-ply) yarn in blue (less than 100g) - G (4mm), H (5mm), I (5.5mm) Crochet Hooks - 4 buttons (2 for securing the diaper cover and 2 for securing the suspenders) - Measuring Tape - Yarn Needle



